The well-hidden Hermit&#39;s Cave in the woods near Nové Bor was not actually habitable
In the north of Bohemia in the foothills of the Lužické Mountains, near Nový Bor in Českolipsk, in the forests through which the Hraběcí cesta led, several sandstone rock formations are hidden.
Natural and man-made.
And we go after the man-made.
The place is called the Hermit&#39;s Cave.
In reality, however, no hermit ever lived here and the cave served as a shelter, or rather a shelter chamber, apparently for grain.
The cave is carved out of the side of a rocky promontory and is accessible by stairs from above.
At the same time, it is practically invisible until the last moment.
It is only revealed by the narrow steps leading to a kind of rock gallery, from where you can only enter the rock.
Although the chamber appears to be quite far from human habitation, at the time of its formation there may have been a field on the plateau where the forest is today.
&quot;The fact that the building does not have a window or even a fireplace located in the traditional location clearly proves that no hermit could ever survive the winter here,&quot; explains historian Kamil Podroužek from the Jan Evangelista Purkyně Faculty of Arts in Ústí nad Labem.
The one-room building has only a stone bench at the back, apparently used for storing containers.
&quot;I see it as a chamber for storing some food or products from the field,&quot; adds Kamil Podroužek.
There are visible traces of tools on the walls of the cave.
Breaking sandstone with a canine was quite simple and quick for the insider.
It was enough to use the joints appropriately and gradually break off the sandstone.
Depending on the length of the canine footprint and the method of cutting in general, the period of the cave&#39;s creation can be roughly determined.
According to the historian, it is probably the end of the 18th century.
The cave is freely accessible and according to the mess that appears in it, nowadays someone sometimes sleeps there.
If you approach the cave from above from one of the forest paths and you are interested in the stream flowing under the cave and the nearby count&#39;s path, you will definitely find the path down as well.
And on the way out of the forest, you might be captivated by the nearby Havraní skaly.
