Vojtěch commented that nothing fundamental is happening, it is not appropriate to talk about declaring a state of emergency or reconvening the crisis team.
In view of the growing number of infected people, the government has once again introduced the obligation to wear masks at indoor events of more than 100 people in the whole of the Czech Republic since Saturday.
From Monday, the capacity of these events will be limited to 500 people, now it is 1000 people.
The government&#39;s approach, where it was not clear until the last moment what measures and when they would come into effect or when they would be announced, was criticized.
&quot;I think that in a situation that is relatively tense, the main actors should instead create a sense of security and, on the contrary, straighten out the confusion,&quot; Senator Marek Hilšer said in Otázky.
