At the beginning of June, the Czech government also approved the so-called traffic lights for Europe, which color-codes the degree of risk of infection in individual European countries and adjusts the rules applicable to entering the Czech Republic from these countries accordingly.
In countries with a low and medium risk, the authorities do not require Czech citizens to have a negative test for the coronavirus or order a quarantine instead, starting from June 15.
