The viper is the only poisonous snake in the Czech Republic, and it is in Šumava that these animals are found in higher numbers, so it is good to be careful when walking.
However, there is no great danger from these animals.
The chance that a viper will bite you is not very high, with normal contact it is afraid of itself.
And if she has room to do so, she likes to crawl away with a loud hiss.
She will only attack if she feels very threatened - for example, if you accidentally step on her.
Even its bite is not a tragedy, although its poison is very effective against small mammals, but it will not kill people.
This can only happen if a person has a particularly weakened organism or suffers from allergies.
