&quot;After being bitten, a person often feels like vomiting, sweats, has an elevated temperature, thirst, abdominal pain and diarrhea, and in weakened individuals and especially allergy sufferers, anaphylactic shock can occur,&quot; Miriam Gredová from the Klatovská hospital explained to Deník.
