But they are here,&quot; said archaeologist Ciprian Ardelean of the University of Zacatecas and lead author of one of two studies published on the subject in the journal Nature.
The youngest tools are 12,500 years old.
According to experts, people inhabited the Chiquihuite cave, located at a high altitude, for 20,000 years.
Until now, the generally accepted theory stated that the first representatives of the species Homo sapiens crossed the land bridge from the region of today&#39;s Russia to Alaska approximately 13,500 years ago.
Archaeological evidence, including unique spear points used to kill mammoths and other prehistoric animals, has shown that this herding culture subsequently spread across much of North America.
But this model has suffered cracks in recent decades, when several ancient settlements were discovered that were two to three thousand years older.
A second study published in the journal Nature describes 42 different sites across North America that prove human presence on the continent as early as 26,000 to 19,000 years ago.
Scientists believe that a small number of people may have arrived on the North American mainland earlier than previously thought.
Some were able to get to America by boat.
&quot;It is clear that people were in America long before the development of the so-called Clovis culture,&quot; said anthropologist Ruth Gruhn from the University of Alberta, Canada, regarding the new findings.
So far, the interest in tickets fulfills an optimistic scenario, according to sellers.
The prices are also gradually decreasing
Ticket sales in the Czech Republic are growing every week.
Compared to last summer, interest is still roughly half, but demand is growing by up to 20 percent every week.
The development after the crisis thus fulfills the most optimistic scenarios according to the sellers.
Air ticket prices are gradually decreasing.
According to the sellers, the most sought-after destinations include mainly southern European countries.
According to data from Kiwi.com, Spain, Italy and Greece are in the lead.
